<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="371" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,438,2011]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,546,571]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The relatively large body size (male body length 
<number box="[883,999,546,571]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="6.785" valueMax="6.82" valueMin="6.75">6.75–6.82</number>
; female body length: 
<number box="[1243,1357,546,571]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="6.375" valueMax="6.4" valueMin="6.35">6.35–6.40</number>
) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[225,1362,417,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[209,1378,409,1716]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 20. Habitus of Metrocoris spp. (apterous males). 13 – 16. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (13: Qingchen mountain; 14: Laojun mountain; 15: Xinmin village; 16: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 17. M. astictus sp. nov.; 18. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 19. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 20. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269715/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">Figs. 19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[195,225,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,524,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1403,517,1753]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 28. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (males). 21 – 24. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (21: Qingchen mountain; 22: Laojun mountain; 23: Xinmin village; 24: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 25. M. astictus sp. nov.; 26. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 27. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 28. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269716/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">27</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[240,272,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 33" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1570,1592]" captionTargetBox="[174,1408,781,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1419,777,1549]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 33. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (females). 29. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 30. M. astictus sp. nov.; 31. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 32. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 33. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm. Figures. 34 – 38. Photographs of abdmen of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in ventral view (females). 34. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 35. M. astictus sp. nov.; 36. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 37. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 38. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269717/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">
<number box="[240,272,583,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
); fore femora only with a subapical indentation and a small single apical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1284,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">
Fig. 
<number box="[1252,1284,583,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
); unmodified inner surface of the fore tibiae (
<figureCitation box="[536,626,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">
Fig. 
<number box="[594,626,619,643]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
); male proctiger with a pair of blackish dots laterally (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1376,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 58" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,207,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1424,193,1276]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 58. Photographs of abdominal segment VIII, pygophore and proctiger of Metrocoris spp. (males). 44, 49, 54. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 45, 50, 55. M. astictus sp. nov.; 46, 51, 56. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 47, 52, 57. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 48, 53, 58. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269719/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">
Fig. 
<number box="[1344,1376,618,643]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="57.0">57</number>
</figureCitation>
); the diagnostic shape of the paramere (
<figureCitation box="[541,635,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 66" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,1438,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[175,1411,1430,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 66. Paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males) in external view. 59 – 62. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (59: Qingchen mountain; 60: Laojun mountain; 61: Xinmin village; 62: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 63. M. astictus sp. nov.; 64. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 65. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 66. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269720/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">Figs. 65</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[648,680,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 83" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,887,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[205,1381,876,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 83. Illustrations of endosoma sclerites (dorsal and lateral views) and paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males). 72 – 74. M. astictus sp. nov.; 75 – 77. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 78 – 80. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 81 – 83. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269722/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">80</figureCitation>
); and female abdominal sternum VII laterally constricted, with the apical half forming a broad lobe, and the caudal margin without median notch (Fig. 
<number box="[1092,1123,691,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="37.0">37</number>
), are the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName box="[181,364,726,750]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guizhouensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[181,364,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">M. guizhouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[370,460,726,751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[370,460,726,751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="371" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,438,2011]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,527,762,787]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">Description. Apterous male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[542,636,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[225,1362,417,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[209,1378,409,1716]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 20. Habitus of Metrocoris spp. (apterous males). 13 – 16. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (13: Qingchen mountain; 14: Laojun mountain; 15: Xinmin village; 16: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 17. M. astictus sp. nov.; 18. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 19. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 20. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269715/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">Figs. 19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[649,681,763,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,524,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1403,517,1753]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 28. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (males). 21 – 24. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (21: Qingchen mountain; 22: Laojun mountain; 23: Xinmin village; 24: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 25. M. astictus sp. nov.; 26. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 27. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 28. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269716/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">27</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<number box="[846,961,762,787]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="6.785" valueMax="6.82" valueMin="6.75">6.75–6.82</number>
, body width (across acetabula) 
<number box="[1317,1368,763,787]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="2.9">2.90</number>
–3.00. Colour: dorsum yellow with prominent black stripes; interocular dark mark usually arrowhead-shaped, bifid posteriorly, along inner margin of eyes with narrowly indistinct dark line; first antennal segment yellowish brown, remaining segments usually blackish; rostrum yellowish with black apex; pronotum with T-shaped black stripe, lateral pronotal stripe very broad; mesonotum with median slender longitudinally stripe, sublateral stripes broader than lateral stripes, nearly equal in width to transverse bands; longitudinal dark stripe of mesopleuron slender, running at least 
<number box="[336,346,979,1003]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[356,371,979,1003]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
of its length, close to anterior margin but far from short acetabular mark; anterior transverse stripe of metanotum laterally confluent with posterior stripe of metanotum; fore femora with apical dark ring and four longitudinal marks, ventral mark connected with ring, remaining marks not confluent, inner mark pale and bright, external mark broad and blackish brown; middle and hind femora yellowish, tibiae and tarsi black; abdomen mainly blackish dorsally, abdominal tergites II–V blackish, abdominal tergites VI–VII blackish anteriorly and yellowish posteriorly; abdominal segment VIII with a large rectangular blackish mark in dorsal view, posteriorly with moderately bifid-shaped. Genital segments yellowish brown. Structural characters: head length 
<number box="[1317,1432,1194,1219]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="0.705" valueMax="0.72" valueMin="0.69">0.69–0.72</number>
, head width 
<number box="[282,396,1230,1255]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="1.6749999999999998" valueMax="1.69" valueMin="1.66">1.66–1.69</number>
, minimum interocular width 
<number box="[724,839,1230,1255]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="0.665" valueMax="0.68" valueMin="0.65">0.65–0.68</number>
; antenna about 
<number box="[1014,1063,1231,1255]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="0.82">0.82</number>
times as long as body, lengths of antennal segments I–IV: 
<number box="[431,483,1266,1291]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="2.57">2.57</number>
, 
<number box="[494,545,1267,1291]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="1.23">1.23</number>
, 
<number box="[557,608,1267,1291]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="1.13">1.13</number>
, 
<number box="[621,673,1266,1291]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="0.61">0.61</number>
; pronotum slightly narrower than head, pronotum length 
<number box="[1317,1432,1266,1291]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="0.685" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.67">0.67–0.70</number>
, pronotum width 
<number box="[340,455,1302,1327]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="1.7650000000000001" valueMax="1.78" valueMin="1.75">1.75–1.78</number>
; fore femora slightly incrassate, ratio length/width 
<number box="[1036,1074,1302,1327]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="5.2">5.2</number>
, inner side not modified, with a subapical indentation, and a small single apical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[764,849,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="371">
Fig. 
<number box="[817,849,1339,1363]" pageId="12" pageNumber="371" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
); inner surface of fore tibiae not modified (
