<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="372" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the name of 
<typeStatus box="[870,918,152,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">type</typeStatus>
locality, Guizhou Province, 
<collectingCountry box="[1238,1309,151,176]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,188,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,426,188,213]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">China</collectingCountry>
(Guizhou) (
<figureCitation box="[563,648,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 84" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1006,1028]" captionTargetBox="[158,1426,202,978]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,984]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 84. Geographical distribution of Metrocoris spp. in this study." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269723/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[616,648,188,212]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,430,223,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Comparative notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[450,638,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guizhouensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[450,638,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">M. guizhouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[650,744,223,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[650,744,223,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
fits the diagnostic characters of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1185,1323,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lituratus">
<emphasis box="[1185,1323,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">M. lituratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[277,531,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" refString="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N. (1993) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I &amp; II. Steenstrupia, 19, 1 - 43, 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">
Chen &amp; Nieser (
<number box="[461,522,260,284]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The paramere shape in this new species is slightly similar to another of our new species, 
<taxonomicName box="[245,369,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astictus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[245,369,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">M. astictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[375,465,295,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[375,465,295,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see above), and both occur in the southern region of the Sichuan Basin. However, the paramere blade of 
<taxonomicName box="[364,549,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guizhouensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[364,549,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">M. guizhouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[557,648,332,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[557,648,332,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is relatively stout, and its subapical part is not curved (
<figureCitation box="[1283,1379,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 66" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,1438,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[175,1411,1430,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 66. Paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males) in external view. 59 – 62. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (59: Qingchen mountain; 60: Laojun mountain; 61: Xinmin village; 62: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 63. M. astictus sp. nov.; 64. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 65. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 66. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269720/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Figs. 65</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1392,1423,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 83" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,887,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[205,1381,876,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 83. Illustrations of endosoma sclerites (dorsal and lateral views) and paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males). 72 – 74. M. astictus sp. nov.; 75 – 77. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 78 – 80. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 81 – 83. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">80</figureCitation>
), whereas the paramere blade of 
<taxonomicName box="[500,623,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astictus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[500,623,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">M. astictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[629,719,367,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[629,719,367,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is much more slender and slightly curved subapically (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1431,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 66" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,1438,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[175,1411,1430,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 66. Paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males) in external view. 59 – 62. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (59: Qingchen mountain; 60: Laojun mountain; 61: Xinmin village; 62: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 63. M. astictus sp. nov.; 64. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 65. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 66. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269720/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Figs. 63</figureCitation>
, 
